Combine textured vegetable protein (TVP) with enough very hot water (about 1/2 cup) to moisten well; let stand 5 minutes; press out excess water with a spoon and set in slow cooker. Rinse and drain beans; add to cooker. Rinse and chop pepper and onion; mince garlic; add to cooker. Heat olive oil in medium nonstick saucepan on medium heat and cook onion, pepper and garlic until onion is translucent for about 3 minutes, transfer to cooker. Add tomato sauce and cook for about 4 hours. Top with shredded cheese and sour cream and serve.